				\begin{document}$${{HI}}_{{above}\,80^\circ {{{\rm{F}}}}}= 	 -42.379+2.04901523\times T+10.14333127\times {RH} \\ 	 -0.22475541\times T\times {RH}-0.00683783\times T\times T \\ 	 -0.05481717\times {{RH}}^{2}+0.00122874\times {T}^{2}\times {RH} \\ 	+0.00085282\times T\times {{RH}}^{2}-0.00000199\times {T}^{2}\times {{RH}}^{2}$$\end{document}HIabove80∘F=−42.379+2.04901523×T+10.14333127×RH−0.22475541×T×RH−0.00683783×T×T−0.05481717×RH2+0.00122874×T2×RH+0.00085282×T×RH2−0.00000199×T2×RH2

Furthermore, when RH is below 13% with temperatures between 80 °F and 112 °F, a reduction adjustment is applied to account for the diminished perceived heat due to dry air:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
