				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${Adjustment}=\left[\left(13-{RH}\right)/4\right]\times \sqrt{\left[17-\left|T-95\right|\right]/17}$$\end{document}Adjustment=13−RH/4×17−T−95/17

Conversely, when RH exceeds 85% with temperatures between 80 °F and 87 °F, an increase adjustment is added to reflect the heightened perception of heat in humid conditions:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
